Allan Gray, business mogul and founder of Allan Gray Investment Management has died. JOHANNESBURG -Â  South African business magnate and founder of the eponymous asset manager, Allan Gray (81), has died. The investment tycoon died as a result of a heart attack over the weekend while in Bermuda. Gray was born in the South African city of East London in 1938. After completing high school at Selborne College, he studied accounting at Rhodes University and went on to earn an MBA at Harvard Business School in 1965. He is survived by his spouse Gill and son William.